  "text": "The analysis of oxygen uptake both in state 3 and in state 4 using glutamate plus malate or succinate as mitochondrial substrate revealed that old rats conserve a normal capacity of substrate oxidation compared with young rats (Table 2) both in heart and liver mitochondria. The preserved respiratory control index was not able to maintain the same membrane potential as that of young rats, which was significantly reduced (Table 1) . These results were consistent with an increased rate of proton conductance, as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
